This paper is about designing more interpretable models in NLP, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed benchmark and metrics for evaluating models could also be relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR) tasks.
